            "value": 2
        },
        "category": "offensive",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> You are holding your wand implement.</p><hr /><p>You fling magical energy at a target within 60 feet, dealing @Damage[(ceil(@actor.level/2)+2)d4[untyped]] damage, with a @Check[reflex|against:thaumaturge|basic] save against your class DC. The damage is of the type you selected when you gained your wand implement. At 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, the damage increases by 1d4.</p>\n<p>You can expend more energy than usual to boost the effect of Fling Magic, dealing @Damage[(ceil(@actor.level/2)+2)d6[untyped]]{d6s of damage} instead of d4s. After you do, the wand's extra energy is discharged; you can't boost the wand's damage again, but can continue to Fling Magic normally. The extra energy recharges at the end of your next turn.</p><hr /><p><strong>Special</strong> This activity has the trait corresponding to the damage type you selected.</p>"
        },
        "publication": {
            "license": "ORC",
            "remaster": true,
            "title": "Pathfinder Dark Archive (Remastered)"
        },
